'''Yahia Fofana''' (born 21 August 2000) is an Ivorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Çaykur Rizespor]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].

== Club career ==

=== Le Havre ===
A product of [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]]'s academy, Fofana signed his first professional contract on 4 July 2019, with the deal lasting until 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=4 July 2019|title=Yahia Fofana signe son premier contrat pro avec Le Havre|trans-title=Yahia Fofana signs his first pro contract with Le Havre|url=https://maligue2.fr/2019/07/04/yahia-fofana-signe-son-premier-contrat-pro-avec-le-havre/|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=31 January 2021|website=maligue2.fr|language=fr}}</ref> His debut came not long after, as he started a [[Coupe de la Ligue]] match against [[Clermont Foot|Clermont]] on 13 August. The match ended in a 4–3 victory for Clermont on penalties after a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Clermont vs. Le Havre - 13 August 2019 - Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/08/13/france/coupe-de-la-ligue/clermont-foot-auvergne/le-havre-athletic-club-football-associat/3082713/|access-date=31 January 2021|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

Fofana's [[Coupe de France]] debut came on 19 January 2021, as his side lost to [[Paris FC]] by a score of 1–0.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Le Havre vs. Paris FC - 19 January 2021 - Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/01/19/france/coupe-de-france/le-havre-athletic-club-football-associat/paris-football-club-98/3441570/|access-date=31 January 2021|website=Soccerway}}</ref> On 30 January, he played his first match in [[Ligue 2]], coming on as a substitute after [[Mathieu Gorgelin]] had been handed a red card in a 0–0 draw away to [[Chamois Niortais F.C.|Chamois Niortais]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Manoury|first=François|date=30 January 2021|title=Ligue 2 : à dix, le HAC résiste à Niort|trans-title=Ligue 2: with ten, HAC resists at Niort|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/ligue-2-a-dix-le-hac-resiste-a-niort-1612041670|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=31 January 2021|website=France Bleu|language=fr}}</ref> In the [[2021–22 Le Havre AC season|2021–22 season]] with Le Havre, he broke into the first team as the starting goalkeeper, surpassing Gorgelin in the pecking order.<ref>{{Cite web|date=13 January 2022|title=Le Havre goalkeeper Yahia Fofana interesting Angers and Fiorentina|url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2022/le-havre-goalkeeper-yahia-fofana-interesting-angers-and-fiorentina/|access-date=13 January 2022|website=Get French Football News}}</ref>

=== Angers ===
On 30 May 2022, Fofana signed a four-year contract with [[Ligue 1]] side [[Angers SCO|Angers]], joining the club upon the expiration of his Le Havre contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 May 2022 |title=Official {{!}} Angers sign goalkeeper Yahia Fofana from Le Havre |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2022/official-angers-sign-goalkeeper-yahia-fofana-from-le-havre/ |access-date=22 June 2022 |website=Get French Football News}}</ref>

While his contract with the Norman club was set to expire in June 2022 and he was being monitored by several French and foreign clubs, Fofana committed to Angers in January, signing a four-year contract effective from July 1, 2022.<ref>{{cite web|date=19 January 2022 |title=Transferts : Yahia Fofana (Le Havre) à Angers pour 4 ans |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-yahia-fofana-le-havre-a-angers-pour-4-ans/1311614 |website=www.lequipe.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> Arriving in Anjou as the first-choice goalkeeper, he was ultimately superseded by [[Paul Bernardoni]] after the summer preseason and started the 2022–23 season on the bench, with Bernardoni starting in goal against [[FC Nantes]] on matchday one, which ended 0–0.

== International career ==
Born in France, Fofana is of Ivorian descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/en/at-a-glance/afcon-2023-yahia-fofana-cote-divoires-future-number-1-goalkeeper/|title=AFCON 2023 - Yahia Fofana: Côte d'Ivoire's future number 1 goalkeeper - At a glance|date=12 August 2023|access-date=30 August 2023|archive-date=23 February 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240223000257/https://sportnewsafrica.com/en/at-a-glance/afcon-2023-yahia-fofana-cote-divoires-future-number-1-goalkeeper/|url-status=dead}}</ref> He has represented France at [[France national under-16 football team|U16]], [[France national under-17 football team|U17]], [[France national under-18 football team|U18]], and [[France national under-19 football team|U19]] level over the years.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Yahia Fofana|url=https://www.fff.fr/equipe-nationale/joueur/9423-fofana-yahia/fiche.html|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 January 2021|website=FFF}}</ref>

Fofana was called up to the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]] for a set of [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] matches in September 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fifciv.com/?q=matchs-civ-les-civ-mal-voici-les-25-el%C3%A9phants-retenus|title=Matchs CIV-LES & CIV-MAL : Voici Les 25 Eléphants Retenus|website=www.fifciv.com|accessdate=30 August 2023}}</ref> He debuted in a 1–0 win over [[Lesotho national football team|Lesotho]] on 9 September 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rti.info/depeches/2023/9/9/la-cote-divoire-bat-le-lesotho-sur-le-score-de-1-but-a-0-au-stade-laurent-pokou-de-san-pedro-le-but-ivoirien-a-ete-inscrit-par-ibrahim-sangare-a-la-16e-minute|title=La Côte d'Ivoire bat le Lesotho sur le score de 1 but à 0 au stade Laurent Pokou de San Pedro. Le but ivoirien a été inscrit par Ibrahim Sangaré à la 16e minute.|first=R. T. I.|last=Info|date=9 September 2023|website=RTI Info|access-date=9 September 2023|archive-date=4 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231004142837/https://www.rti.info/depeches/2023/9/9/la-cote-divoire-bat-le-lesotho-sur-le-score-de-1-but-a-0-au-stade-laurent-pokou-de-san-pedro-le-but-ivoirien-a-ete-inscrit-par-ibrahim-sangare-a-la-16e-minute|url-status=dead}}</ref>

In December 2023, Fofana was named to the Ivory Coast's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]]. He played in all matches but the opening one. Ivory Coast ended up winning the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/federationivoiriennedefootball/posts/pfbid02GVkTYXjhv2yBQizHRNxngTGoMrFLXgcUg3kQeXgEk3gZ158w6cxqRFjDBXCCU3ihl|title=LA LISTE|publisher=[[Ivorian Football Federation]]|date=28 December 2023|access-date=28 December 2023|language=pt|via=Facebook}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.7info.ci/cote-divoire-voici-les-27-elephants-de-gasset-zaha-et-des-tenors-font-leurs-adieux-a-la-can-2023/|title=Côte d'Ivoire: voici les 27 Eléphants de Gasset, Zaha et des ténors font leurs adieux à la CAN 2023|publisher=[[7info]]|first=Tristan|last=Sahi|date=28 December 2023|access-date=28 December 2023|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/media/ow2obxrw/c%C3%B4te-divoire.pdf|title=CÔTE D'IVOIRE|publisher=Confederation of African Football|date=5 January 2024}}</ref>

Fofana is included in the list of Ivorian players selected by head coach [[Emerse Faé]] to participate in the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=Nicolas Pépé et Simon Adingra absents, Wilfried Zaha de retour : la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la CAN |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Nicolas-pepe-et-simon-adingra-absents-wilfried-zaha-de-retour-la-liste-de-la-cote-d-ivoire-pour-la-can/1615689 |website=www.lequipe.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=CAN 2025: la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire, tenante du titre, avec le retour de Wilfried Zaha |url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20251209-can-2025-la-liste-de-la-c%C3%B4te-d-ivoire-tenante-du-titre-avec-le-retour-de-wilfried-zaha |website=www.rfi.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On May 15, 2026, Fofana was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Faé]] in his list of 26 players in order to participate in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

